.TH "drm_sysfs_connector_status_event" 9 "drm_sysfs_connector_status_event" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_sysfs_connector_status_event \- generate a DRM uevent for connector property status change
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_sysfs_connector_status_event
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "struct drm_property *property "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
connector on which property status changed
.IP "property" 12
connector property whose status changed.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a uevent for the DRM device specified by \fIdev\fP.  Currently we
set HOTPLUG=1 and connector id along with the attached property id
related to the status change.
